e YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"pe_now":42.8,"pe_percentile":100.0,"median_pe":27.6,"earnings_yield_pct":2.34,"pb":4.11,"ev_ebitda":19.93,"quality_score":71.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":null,"peg":null,"cheapness":{"status":"weak","read":"P/E at the 100-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 expensive vs its own history."},"expectations":"Trades at 42.8\u00d7 earnings; multi-year growth not estimable, so 'priced-in' growth is unclear.","cyclical_caveat":null,"meaning":"P/E percentile = where today's price-to-earnings sits within the stock's own last-10-yr range (low = cheap vs its past). Paired with the Quality score and 5-yr profit growth so a cheap multiple is judged against business strength, not in isolation.","why_useful":"Cheapness only matters relative to quality and growth \u2014 a low P/E on a declining or peak-cyclical business is a trap, not a bargain.","why_it_can_fail":"P/E breaks for loss-makers / one-offs; for banks use P/B not EV/EBITDA; a multiple cheap vs history can stay cheap if the business has structurally de-rated."},"ownership":{"ok":true,"na":null,"holders":{"Promoter":{"periods":["Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[73.01,73.01,66.46,66.46],"latest_pct":66.46,"chg_1y_pp":-6.55},"FII":{"periods":["Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[6.78,7.67,8.9,8.86],"latest_pct":8.86,"chg_1y_pp":2.08},"DII":{"periods":["Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[7.12,4.0,9.27,10.16],"latest_pct":10.16,"chg_1y_pp":3.04},"Public":{"periods":["Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[13.08,15.32,15.37,14.51],"latest_pct":14.51,"chg_1y_pp":1.43}},"pledge":null,"events":[{"date":"22-Aug-2025","subject":"Dividend - Rs 0.55 P